title: Jackson Custom Shop USA King V - KV2 - 1 Hum - 24 Fret - Goat Skull -  2017 w Original Jackson HSC
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this simply wicked Jackson USA Custom Shop King V with Goat Skull / Pentagram graphic.

The Jackson King V is a classic Jackson design and has become an iconic guitar in the metal world. This Jackson Custom Shop masterpiece has 24 Jumbo Frets to reach the full two octaves. It features a quartersawn through-body painted maple neck, and the phenomenally fast feel of its compound-radius ebony fingerboard (12"-16") is simply breathtaking. This guitar begs to be played!

Other premium features include a single DiMarzio Tone Zone Humbucker in the bridge humbucking pickup which produces high gain heavy tones yet cleans up nicely. It is perfect for metal and rock. In addition, it has a single volume knob, Floyd Rose Original locking nut and double-locking two-point tremolo, ivoroid fingerboard and headstock binding, black hardware, black headstock with white Jackson logo, and mother of pearl shark fin inlays on it's perfect ebony neck. 

Our King V comes to us in excellent condition. There are some minor signs of player wear but no serious dings or scratches. Even the points of the V are remarkably ding free!!! The only chip or real blemish on the guitar is on one of the back beveled edges and pictured above. One of the case hinges has been damaged. All of the latches and other hinges function perfectly. 

The guitar has been freshly set up with Dunlop .10-.46 strings in standard tuning. Ships in original Jackson molded hard shell case.

title: Marshall 1974X Handwired 1 x 12" 18watt Combo Amp and Matching Marshall CX 1 x 12" Extension Cab
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this Marshall 1974X Handwired 1 x 12" 18 watt Combo Amp and matching Marshall CX extension cab. 

Our Marshall comes to us in excellent condition and sounds amazing! To really get this amp and extension cab talking you'll want to wind it up a bit! Luckily it's 18 watt output power allows for killer cranked Marshall tones at a reasonable volume level! Ships with original footswitch.

Marshall Handwired 1974X at a Glance:
  • The 1974X 1 x 12" combo amp: an authentic re-issue
  • Aged Greenback T1221 speakers
  • Original components live up to point-to-point perfection

The 1974X 1 x 12" combo amp: an authentic reissue
The 1974X is an authentic reissue of the fabled model 1974 combo of the late sixties (1966-1968). Just like the original, it boasts a point-to-point, handwired, tagboard circuit housed in an aluminum chassis, plus a valve-driven tremolo circuit. At the very heart of its simple yet effective 2-channel design can be found six valves: two ECC83s in V1 and V2, a 12AT7 in V3 (Phase Inverter) an EZ81 rectifier, and a pair of cathode biased EL84s in the power stage. As the output and mains transformers are vital components in any amplifier as they influence performance, sound, and feel, Marshall worked extremely closely with their associates at Dagnall in order to duplicate the original, off-the-shelf transformers in all areas.

Aged Greenback T1221 speakers
A contributing sonic factor in the original 1974 is the way the sound of the Celestion Greenback speaker softens with age. For the 1974X, Celestion revisited the recipe for the original Greenback T1221 speaker, and aged it. The result is a new speaker proprietary to Marshall.

Original components live up to point-to-point perfection
This new series was created to meet growing public demand and to pay homage to models that, for many players, represent the ultimate in organic, all-valve guitar tone. The primary objective was to achieve maximum authenticity in terms of components, circuitry, construction methods, materials, specifications, aesthetics, signal path, performance, tonal characteristics, and feel. All of the original components and materials were used or reproduced, and the original methods of construction employed in the late 1960s were revisited. All transformers - output and power - have been meticulously re-created by Dagnall Electronics, and each amplifier's handwired tag-board lives up to the idea of point-to-point perfection.

Marshall Handwired 1974X Features:
  • 18-watt, 16-ohm, mono 1 x 12" combo amp
  • Exclusive, aged reissue of the original 20-watt, ceramic magnet, Celestion Greenback T1221 12" speaker
  • Replica of the grey and white striped Bluesbreaker grille cloth used on the originals
  • High-grade baltic birch cabinet with finger-locked joints
Marshall CX 1 x 12" Extension Cab
This beautifully hand-soldered 20W extension cabinet pairs perfectly with the handwired 1974X combo. It features a single 12” Celestion G12M-20 Greenback speaker, specially aged to flawlessly capture that vintage 60’s vibe. With its old-school fret and classic piping, you’ll look and feel like you’re playing an original 1974 combo.

The amp and extension cab are in fantastic shape but there are some scuffs on the tolex visible in the photos above.

title: Ibanez TSA15H Tube Screamer 15W Tube Guitar Amp Head And Matching TSA112C 1x12 Cab 2010
description:
Ibanez TSA15H 15W Tube Amplifier and Matching TSA12C 1X12 Cab made in 2010.


“The Ibanez TSA15H amplifier head combines real all-tube tone with the classic distortion and drive of a TS9 Tube Screamer pedal. A pair of 12AX7s and a pair of 6V6 power tubes drive the TSA15H, providing gentle breakup when pushed. For rich fuzz and gritty overdrive, kick on the Tube Screamer circuit. Dual operation (15-watt pentode or 5-watt triode) gives you even more flexibility, allowing you to dial in the headroom you need to play in many different environments. Matched up with a TSA112C speaker cabinet, the TSA15H has enough output to comfortably carry midsize and larger venues. If you're looking for a flexible tube amp head for a great price, then the Ibanez TSA15H is an excellent choice.”


“Looking for a classic 1 x 12" to go with your TSA15H Tube Screamer head? Check this out: the Ibanez TSA112C. The TSA112C is an 80-watt guitar speaker cabinet that comes loaded with a 12" Celestion Seventy 80 speaker. This classic speaker provides tight low end with punchy midrange and aggressive bite. If you want to get the most out of your TSA15H Tube Screamer head, then match it up with an Ibanez TSA112C cabinet.”

description:
Fender Custom Shop ’60 Stratocaster reissue in Olympic White finish NOS with light relic made in 2007. This guitar features an alder body, maple neck and rosewood fingerboard. Equipped with 3 Fender Custom Shop single-coil pickups controlled by a master volume and two tone controls complete with a 5-way pickup selector switch. The 25.5” scale length neck has an oval 60’s C shape neck profile with 21 vintage style frets and a 7.25” fingerboard radius. The lightly relic’d Olympic White finish and nickel hardware give the appearance, feel, and tone of an original 1965 Fender Stratocaster complete with vintage spec’d Kluson style tuning machines and a vintage style synchronized tremolo. The mint green pick-guard and vintage style brown tolex custom shop hardshell case give the finishing touches of a Strat from the early 60’s.

This guitar is in very good condition however there is finish checking throughout the body that may or may not have been form the factory which we have seen factory aging with some vintage reissue NOS models. Aside from the finish checking there are a couple of small dings as well as some natural play-wear such as guitar pick marks (see photos). This guitar has been freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning. Comes with the original hard-shell case, COA, leather strap, case candy, springs, and tremolo cover.

title: Dr. Z MAZ 38 Senior NR Head 2011
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this wicked little DR. Z

The Dr. Z Maz Sr 38 NR is an ever versatile guitar amplifier that has been gracing large stages and corner clubs for years. The 38 NR will give you plenty of clean headroom and sweet driven tones for stages of all sizes. The 38 NR features a split load cathode biased output section which yields an authority not heard in many EL84 powered amps. Compared to the reverb equipped Maz 38 you get more drive and low end thrust. The NR has a very rich dynamic gain with a tight bottom and superb clarity. It's an excellent choice for discerning rock and roots music players.

The front panel features Volume, Treble, Middle, Bass, Master, and the ever versatile Cut control. The back panel features a 4, 8, and 16 ohm speaker out. An effects loop is also standard. The 38 NR is powered by a quartet of cathode biased EL84s, has three 12AX7s in the front end, and a 5AR4 rectifier. With 38 watts at your finger tips, you can move enough air to get your guitar out in front of the band.

The Dr. Z MAZ-38 is a truly versatile amp for the working or studio musician. Whether your forte' is Blues, Country, Roots, or Rock, The MAZ 38 Senior will fit the bill.

title: Fender Custom Shop John 5 Bigsby Telecaster Autographed Guitar & Strap 2008
description:
Fender Custom Shop John 5 Signature model Telecaster in Gloss Black finish with matching headstock made in 2008. This very cool guitar features a double bound select ash body with a maple neck and rosewood fingerboard. Equipped with a Seymour Duncan “Hot-Rails” in the bridge position and a Fender Custom Shop “Twisted Tele” Single-coil in the neck position controlled by a master volume & master tone knob with a 3-way pickup selector. The all chrome hardware looks evil in the dark and blinding in the light which is perfect for any live gig! The tuning machines are Fender locking deluxe tuners which make changing strings with the factory Bigsby a breeze as well as hold excellent tuning stability. The chrome pick-guard, chrome bridge, chrome knurled knobs and chrome control plate all mold together with the dark gloss black finish with maching headstock for a work of art that shows constant reflections. The 25.5” scale length neck has a 12” fingerboard radius, a modern C shape neck profile, 22 frets and white dot inlays. The previous owner was able to have John 5 sign the guitar and the strap with a photo included of him and John 5 at a meet & greet provided. This signature perviously was personalized “To Mike” however we were able to removed this part pf the signature without damaging the original guitar finish.

This guitar is in excellent condition and is a fantastic guitar whether you are a player, a fan of John 5 or a fan of extremely cool guitars. The signature on the body was done very tastefully and was done in a spot where you can still play the guitar without constantly rubbing against it. If you do not care for the signature it is easily removable. There are minor surface scratches, and skuffs but they are very light and very difficult to see with the naked eye or photograph. The gloss black finish and mirror hardware show fingerprints and scratches very easily so while this guitar is clean now, it can become dirty and show flaws very quickly if you are not careful. This guitar also comes with a guitar strap signed by John 5, the COA and the original hardshell case with crushed red velvet interior. Freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning this guitar shreds and is ready to rock!

title: Fender Custom Shop '69 Stratocaster Relic Masterbuilt Jason Smith Floyd Rose 2009 Pink Over Black
description:
Fender Custom Shop ’69 Stratocaster Relic Masterbuilt by Jason Smith finished in pink over black with a factory aged Floyd Rose Tremolo. This is one of the most outrageous and cool Fender Masterbuilt Stratocasters we have ever come across, but of course here at Diablo Guitars we are fans of the loud and outrageous guitars of the 80’s. This 4-bolt ’69 Reissue Strat begins with an alder body, maple neck, rosewood fingerboard and the large 70’s style headstock. The finish is a pink over black relic that digs into the bare wood in certain spots and gives an overall zero f***$ given attitude. The factory Floyd Rose has been aged to the point of rusted parts (that are still fully functional and purely aesthetic) which bleeds a bit even into the white pick-guard with light rust residue (builder Jason Smith really went that far). Some other minor details that would ordinarily go unnoticed are the splashes of pink on the aged white knobs to show where the refinish would have accidentally sprayed onto the knobs.

Equipped with a Seymour Duncan SH-4 Humbucker in the bridge and Abigail Ybarra hand-wound ’69 single coils in the middle and neck positions with a 5-way switch and an S-1 switch for a large variety of coil tapping and pickup splitting capabilities. The chrome hardware consists of Fender ’69-early 70’s style components including the “F” tuning machines, an “F” 4-bolt neck plate, and the afore mentioned aged chrome Floyd Rose. The 25.5 scale length neck has a medium C shape neck profile that is a little bit beefier than most modern Strats with a very well worn finish on the back of the neck. Mother of pearl dot inlays, 21 vintage narrow frets, and a great looking and feeling rosewood fingerboard.

This guitar is in excellent condition and although it is a relic there appears to be some pick scratches that may or may not have been factory, it is hard to tell given how detailed Jason Smith got when building this masterpiece. Freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge stings and setup in standard tuning with low action and ready to shred! This guitar play absolutely fantastic! This is one of the coolest Fender Custom Shop Masterbuilts that we have ever seen and we needed to have it come through our shop! Comes with the original Fender Custom Shop late 60’s hardshell case with orange interior and COA.

title: Hughes & Kettner Duotone Tommy Thayer Signature Amp Head And Cab 2008 Germany W/COA
description:
Hughes & Kettner Tommy Thayer Signature Edition Duotone 100-watt Head And Cab. This amp is in excellent condition, and includes amp covers, original footswitch, COA Signed by Tommy Thayer, Tommy Thayer Signature edition amp poster, stickers and booklets.


The amp of choice for KISS guitarist Tommy Thayer.

KISS guitarist Tommy Thayer found his tube amp of choice in the Hughes & Kettner Duotone. In fact, he was so enthused to chance upon an amp so good that he put his name on a Duotone Signature Series model. It now adorns the amp head's shining blue Plexiglas front panel, alongside his official KISS logo.


Duotone delivers to-die-for tone, but takes the one-sound-wonder of vintage amps a significant step further. When it set out to design this modern classic guitar amp head, DuoTone collaborated with an amp-tuning specialist to embrace the pros' most frequently requested modifications. The top four demands are more tone, more attack, a tube-driven effects loop, and a clean channel that merits its name.


DuoTone went on to build the first off-the-rack amp to offer all of these special tweaks as standard features: You get supercharged classic rock tones thick enough to slice with fat, dynamic overdrive, a top-drawer clean channel, a tubedriven effects loop, and even a dual master.


Hughes & Kettner's tube amps all have distinctive personalities tailored to individual expression. Built for tube purists, each amp head, including the Tommy Thayer Signature Amp is a no-frills, straightforward original. Each packed with quality of components and an aesthetic design.


Duotone guitar amps have a no-compromise design that deliver your favorite classic rock sounds. As its name suggests, the Duotone offers two distinct tonal worlds. There's the rough-and-ready overdrive channel that packs a mighty wallop and the clean channel with dynamics galore. Plus, with the benefit of the overdrive channel's boost circuit, you have enormous gain reserves to dial in everything from a touch of grit for classic rock riffing to high gain for singing leads. The Tommy Thayer Duotone amp head delivers tube tone pure and simple”even the parallel effects loop is served by a tube. There is not a single transistor in the entire signal path.


The hallmarks of the Hughes & Kettner Duotone amps are not only its exceptional sound quality but also its reliability and stage-worthiness. All amps and amp heads from the custom tube series ship with tubes that satisfy the highest standards for quality and assure maximum reliability under even the most arduous operating conditions.

title: EVH 5150 III 6L6 3-Channel 50-Watt 2x12" Guitar Combo 2018 - 2020 Ivory
description:
EVH 5150 III 50W 6L6 2X12 Tube Combo in Ivory. Amp is Excellent Condition, however there is a ding in front of cab (see pics)


Brimming with brawny tone, the EVH® 5150III® 50W 6L6 212 Combo is arena-sized sound in a Celestion® powered compact package for more convenient transport.

Redesigned with versatile, all-new independent dual- concentric controls that allow for gain and volume level matching, this 50-watt tube combo amp boasts three channels for any playing style— crisp cleans, raw crunch or searing leads.

Delivering a full-spectrum of tone, channel one features pristine cleans, channel two kicks in with overdrive and heavy gain similar to the EVH 5150III 100S, while channel three oozes with liquid distortion. Channels one and two each have dual concentric gain/volume controls, with shared EQ (low, mid, high). Channel three has its own gain, volume and EQ (low, mid, high) controls. All three channels also have global presence, resonance and reverb controls.

Loaded with dual 12” custom special designed EVH Celestion speakers to enhance and refine both your sound and your style, this combo amp also has seven JJ ECC83 (12AX7) preamp tubes, two JJ 6L6 power tubes and front-panel adjustable power output from 50 watts down to one watt.

Other features include a single input, rear-panel selectable output impedance (4, 8 or 16 ohms) with a pair of parallel speaker outputs, rear-panel MIDI input and preamp output, rear-panel effects loop and headphone jack (mutes power amp), and a four-button footswitch that controls all three channels and reverb for easy onstage switching.

The cabinet is constructed out of birch with special internal baffling for tight and increased bass response. Wrapped in stylish Black or Ivory vinyl, the EVH 5150III 50W 6L6 212 Combo is finished off with vintage-style chicken-knobs, red LED jewel indicator, molded black plastic top handle and pop-out casters.

description:
Gretsch G6128-CS Custom Shop - Masterbuilt by Stephen Stern - Duo Jet - Book Matched Claro Walnut Top - NAMM Exclusive - 2019 - Natural

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this absolutely stunning Duo Jet from the Gretsch USA Custom Shop. Hand built by master luthier Stephen Stern, this beauty features a magnificent book matched claro walnut top. The body and sides are the traditional Gretsch Duo Jet mahogany but this one has not been chambered! It weighs in at an impressive 9 lbs 8.5 oz and you can hear and feel it in the remarkable TONE. This is mated to a mahogany set neck featuring a beautiful ebony fretboard. The culmination of these tone woods and craftsmanship is instantly apparent as you play this resonant tone machine...and that's before you've plugged it in.

Rounded out with TV Jones Power Tron pickups in both the neck and bridge, open back Gotoh Vintage Style tuners, a Tune-O-Matic style bridge with a gorgeous "V" stop tail piece, this guitar absolutely sings when plugged in. Remarkably versatile and incredibly musical. Clean, overdriven and all points in between. This amazing Masterbuilt Duo Jet does it all with ease, warmth, depth and punch. The Gretsch shallow "U" neck profile is incredibly comfortable to play and the vintage style Gretsch frets only take it one step farther.

This beautiful guitar is in MINT condition with out a single visible scratch nick or ding. It was freshly set up with D'Addario .10-.46 strings and low fast easy action. Ships in it's original tweed Gretsch Custom Shop Case and includes certificate of authenticity, hang tags and all original case candy.

This remarkable Duo Jet from Master Builder Stephen Stern is a really special guitar. Top to bottom, front to back the Gretsch USA Custom Shop delivers the goods strait from their hands and into yours.

model: Custom Shop Jimi Hendrix Signature Strat Journeyman Relic
title: Fender Custom Shop Jimi Hendrix 'Voodoo Child' Strat Journeyman Relic w Case Candy, COA, and OHSC
description:
Jimi Hendrix was the quintessential innovator of modern music. A left-handed player who wielded a right handed-guitar, he rewrote the vocabulary of contemporary guitarists with the fiery tone of his “upside-down”, reverse-strung instrument. The sounds he created with his Strat informed his inventive technique—and in turn his songwriting—in a synergistic relationship that birthed a legend. The Voodoo Child Strat is your chance to directly experience the tone and essential configuration of his guitars, recreated for right-handed players by the artisans of the Fender Custom Shop.

The Voodoo Child Strat takes a multi-faceted approach to recreating the elements of Hendrix’s unique configuration, the most obvious being the reversed headstock. Reversing the headstock lengthens the distance between the nut and low-E string for a tighter playing feel, simultaneously shortening the distance between the nut and the high-E for easier bending and vibrato. The trio of left-handed hand-wound Custom Shop ’69 Strat single-coil pickups reverse the pole piece placement, creating inspiring tone with enhanced upper harmonics and definition. Reversing the angle of the bridge pickup gives it the same orientation as a left-handed Strat strung upside down, giving you all the elements of the Hendrix sound and feel for your own.

Other features include a two-piece select alder body, Journeyman Relic nitrocellulose lacquer finish, tinted maple neck with ’65 Strat “Oval C”-shaped profile, 9.5”-radius fingerboard, 21 6105 frets, 5-way switching, vintage wiring, 3-ply Eggshell pickguard, American Vintage Synchronized Tremolo, vintage-style tuning machines with Fender logo, bone nut and wing string tree. Includes deluxe hardshell case, strap and Certificate of Authenticity.

This Voodoo Child Strat comes to us in dead mint condition. This guitar is in “like-new” mint condition and was purchased as a B-stock from a Fender dealer. It's been freshly set up with .09-.42 strings and plays like an absolute dream. All the original case candy, floor traveler and COA are included.

description:
This rare and beautiful ESP "Vintage Plus" is a gorgeous and unique guitar indeed. 

Featuring a swamp ash body finished in a beautiful trans red, this lighter and magnificent tone wood makes for a punchy and resonant guitar acoustically. A maple neck with rosewood fretboard in a 12" radius makes this guitar instantly feel like an old friend in your hands. It plays like a dream. 

Plugged in the fun continues, the guitar is loaded with a Seymour Duncan JB in the bridge, Hot Rails in the middle and finally a Duncan SH 1 in the neck. Via a 5-Way blade switch a deep arsenal of serious tones are available with little to no effort. A Fishman / Wilkinson piezo saddle tremolo bridge has been added and is accessible via a toggle switch on the face of the guitar (stereo cable included) allowing you to pull lush acoustic tones out of the guitar with ease. 

The guitar has been freshly set up with D'Addario .10-.46 strings in standard tuning with low fast action.  Ships with stereo cable in it's original ESP hard shell case. It's in excellent condition with some very minor signs of player wear (scuffs and scratches in the finish). The trem spring cover has been cut off to allow easy access for re-stringing the guitar. One of the saddle height screws is missing it's small cap but functions perfectly via an allen wrench.

title: Supro Vintage 1965 Thunderbolt - S6420 - 15" 35watt Combo Amp with RCA Glass and Jensen C15P
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this 1965 Supro Thunderbolt S6420 15" 35watt Combo Amp!

S6420 Thunderbolt—Two knobs and the TRUTH! Renowned for its bold, full-range sound and up-front, honest midrange, the Thunderbolt covers a remarkable spectrum of vintage tone while wringing every ounce of personality from whatever guitar is plugged in. From clean jazz to Tele twang, soapbar blues to humbucker grind, the Thunderbolt dishes out 35 Watts of “Class A” tube tone from its vintage Supro dual 6L6 power plant. A 5U4 rectifier tube is employed to deliver that unmistakable high-powered vintage sag. Normal and Extra-hot input options, combined with a wide range of available gain on tap, allow you to fine-tune the texture and response of this amp’s massive sound. Turned all the way up, the Thunderbolt exhibits nearly zero self-noise; yet it puts out enough volume to be easily heard on large venue and theater stages, with overdrive completely controlled by the guitar’s volume knob.

Our Thunderbolt comes to us in excellent condition. It was recently serviced at Solderhaus Vintage Tube Repair where the following items were expertly replaced: Power Supply Electrolytic Capacitors, Bypass Electrolytic Capacitors. The Vintage Jensen C15P speaker has been carefully restored an is 100% pure vintage spec. All pots and sockets have been carefully cleaned to ensure 100% perfect functionality. The amp has all vintage RCA glass in it - 2 x RCA 12AX7 - 2 X RCA 6L6GC - and one Dumont 5U4 Rectifier Tube. (All pictured above)

  • Normal and Hot inputs

title: Vox AC15 C1 Custom 2 Channel 15 Watt 1x12 Guitar Combo 2008 Limited Edition in Black and Red Tolex
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this rare and clean, killer sounding Vox AC 15 C1 Limited Edition amplifier.

The VOX AC15 is the amp that started it all. Boasting both a Normal and Top Boost channel, the AC15 Custom is an all-tube, EL84 driven workhorse that delivers 15 watts of authentic British tone into your choice of a genuine Celestion Greenback or Alnico Blue speaker. The AC15 Custom also offers footswitchable spring reverb and classic VOX tremolo to enhance the already impressive sound. Adored by the biggest names in music for nearly 60 years, the VOX AC15 Custom carries on the tradition that began in 1958 and offers guitarists the unmistakable sound of VOX, with all the refinements of a modern amplifier.

Our AC 15 C1 comes to us in remarkably clean condition in the rare "Red and Black" tolex layout. There are some very minor scuffs in the tolex visible in the photos above, but beyond these this is essentially a new amp!!! It does not ship with a footswitch. The footswitch is sold separately from Vox and all Vox dealers. The amp did not come in to us with a footswitch.

title: Fender Limited Edition American Professional Strat HSS Shawbucker 2019 Rosewood Neck Gold Rose Gold
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this breathtaking Fender Limited Edition American Professional Stratocaster with a solid Rosewood neck! 

Often copied, but never surpassed, the Stratocaster is arguably the world’s most-loved electric guitar. Electrifying the music world since its release in 1954, its natural, versatile sound made the Stratocaster the benchmark for exceptional guitar tones. The American Professional Stratocaster HSS ShawBucker isn’t a re-imagining of the classic design; it’s the authentic original model, evolved. The fat-sounding ShawBucker humbucking bridge pickup is joined by tone wizard Tim Shaw’s latest vintage-informed design—the V-Mod single-coil pickups. These brand-new pickups are voiced specifically for each position, mixing alnico magnet types to produce powerful, nuanced tones with original Fender sonic DNA. Retain high end clarity when adjusting the volume controls, thanks to the new treble-bleed tone circuit that lets your tone shine through in all its glory. The new modern “Deep C”-shaped neck profile feels just right in your hand while the narrow-tall frets make it easy to bend strings accurately and play perfectly intonated chords. 

Our Strat comes to us in remarkably clean condition with no visible dings or signs of serious player wear. It's been freshly set up with .09-.42 strings in standard tuning and plays like an absolute dream. Ships in it's original Fender molded hard shell case.

title: Gibson Memphis ES-335 Satin Red with Certificate of Authenticity and Original Hard Shell Case
description:
Just in at Diablo Guitars is this absolutely killer Gibson Memphis ED-335 in satin red. 

The legendary ES-335 is sweeter than ever in the 2017 Gibson Memphis edition! Advancements in vintage coloring, a sustain-enhancing historic tubeless truss rod, and PAF-evoking Burstbucker pickups make this 335 look, play, and feel more like an original '58 than ever. From soulful blues to smooth jazz to gritty rock, there's just no substitution for the vibrant sustain and all-night comfort of the 335's contoured maple body with feedback-fighting center block. A more stable redesigned neck with rolled binding gives the Gibson Memphis 335 a smoother feel, and an adjustable ABR-1 bridge with titanium saddles helps accommodate the roughest to the most delicate of playing styles. Experience the instrument that shaped the sound of rock 'n' roll: the Gibson Memphis ES-335.

Nobody makes a semi-hollowbody guitar like Gibson. This superb 335 is handcrafted in Gibson's Memphis Custom Shop on Beale Street for quality craftsmanship you can count on, and from a city that knows how blues should sound. Carefully selected maple and poplar tone woods give the Gibson Memphis 335 its signature bark, and a carefully calipered body cavity with Titebond 50 glue joints and a maple center block give it its controlled howl and haunting sustain.

Handwound Burstbuckers give this ES-335 the tight low end, complex midrange, and sweet highs of Gibson's vintage PAF ("Patent Applied For") pickups with extra clarity and power. Historically mismatched rhythm and lead pickups give each position a unique flavor for chords and leads, while pairing the pickups together unlocks a sweetness that even Gibson purists will appreciate.

Our 335 comes to us in excellent condition! There are two small nicks on one of the horn edges (documented in the photos above). The hardware is a bit cloudy and shows some signs of player wear and there are also a few very minor scuffs on the back, but really, the guitar is remarkably clean given it's age!

It's been freshly set up with D'Addario .10-.46 strings in standard tuning with low fast action and plays like butter. Ships in it's original Gibson hard shell case and includes and alternate pick guard, truss rod cover (one screw hoop is snapped off the spare) Gibson warranty and check list pamphlet and certificate of authenticity.

title: Gibson SG Elite Metallic Sunset Rose Pink Tim Shaw Humbuckers 1988 OHSC
description:
Gibson SG Elite in Sunset Metallic (Pink) finish made in 1988. This is a very clean and 100% original example of a very rare and beautiful Gibson SG Elite. The SG Elite features a solid Honduran Mahogany body, a one-piece Honduran Mahogany neck with angled heel, and a bound ebony fingerboard. This particular guitar that dates to the 74th day in 1988 is one of the last SG Elite’s to com stock with the Tim Shaw designed Gibson Humbuckers with Alnico V magnets which would shortly after be replaced by the Bill Lawrence designed circuit board pickups. These iconic patent stamped pickups paired with the original pots that date to 1987 sound killer giving a mixture of a classic yet aggressive sounding PAF tones with distortion as well as crystal clear clean tones. The control layout is comprised of 2 volume and 1 tone controls with a mini coil-tap switch in place of where the 2nd tone knob would ordinarily be on a Gibson SG and of course a 3-way pickup selector switch.

The 24.75” scale length neck has a slim taper neck profile measuring .800” at the 1st fret and .875” at the 12th fret. The 22 original frets still have plenty of life left as this guitar has been treated as a case queen. with very little play-wear. The mother of pearl block inlays look striking on the dark black ebony fingerboard and match the mother of pearl “crown” and “Gibson” logo headstock inlays. This guitar came stock with a locking nut as well as a TP-6 tailpiece both of which keep the guitar’s tuning locked in place with adjustments if needed via the fine-tuners. The Grover Rotomatic tuning machines, 5-ply custom pick-guard, and black with gold top-hat reflector knobs are the finish touches in the very elegant looking SG elite. This guitar’s factory finish is very vibrant, and although the color is called “Sunset Metallic” it is really more of a metallic rose/pink color that brightens to an almost sparkle finish in the light. I tried to show a variation of light exposure in the photos to give a better idea of the finish. 

This guitar is excellent condition and almost flawless, however with age there are some minor surface scratches, a small ding on the back of the neck, a few very light belt buckle marks and some light tarnishing of the gold plated hardware. Freshly setup with 10-46 gauge strings and setup with super low shredding action this guitar plays phenomenally well! If you prefer your string height setup higher we can make any adjustments as you wish, but this guitar at the moment is meant for a shredder! Comes with the original hardshell case which is brown tolex with pink blanket interior and matches the guitar finish nicely!

title: Gibson Les Paul LPR8S 1958 Reissue R8 2016 Iced Tea Burst Flame Top W/OHSC
description:
Gibson Custom Shop Les Paul 1958 (R8S)Flame Top in Iced Ted Burst made in 2016. This guitar features a solid one-piece mahogany body, a beautiful flame carved maple top, a one-piece mahogany neck, and a bound rosewood fingerboard. The 24.75” scale length neck has the iconic ’58 rounded neck profile, 22 historic frets, and a period correct long neck tenon using hide glue.

This 1958 reissue uses all of the most historically accurate hardware available which include the Kluson Deluxe single-line single-ring tuning machines with pearloid tulip machine heads, gold top hat knobs, single-ply cream pick-guard and nickel ABR-1 bridge with stop tailpiece. The electronics feature the very best in vintage accurate historic specs which include Bumblbee capacitors, CTS pots, and the infamous un-potted Gibson PAF replica “Custombucker” Humbucker pickups. The Gibson Custombucker pickups are only made available through guitars that are produced by the Gibson Custom Shop with the Custombuckers installed in the guitar and are not available for purchase aftermarket.

The guitar is in excellent condition with only minor surface scratches, there is a very light scratch near the toggle switch, there is a light scuff on the tip of the horn and the rear cavity cover has some marks on it which you can see better in pictures than in person(see photos).

Comes with the original Gibson hardshell case which is a very cool Brown tolex 5-latch thermometer case with pink interior, COA, hang tags, and case candy.

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this stunning 2004 Hamer Vector Flying V. The Korina '1958' style flying V that is a real show stopper!
As with all of the Korina series instruments made by Hamer in this era, the quality of materials and craftsmanship is absolutely top shelf. These instruments are among the best ever built by the company. The guitar is remarkably resonant. When unplugged it's spanky, punchy and warm. It's truly awe inspiring from the first few notes played. It's a true testament to the quality of this guitar.
Plugged in it only gets better. This Korina V is loaded with a Seymour Duncan 59 in the bridge and a Duncan 59 in the neck as well. The pickups collide with the gorgeous tone woods for a smooth, silky tone that is nothing short of inspiring. From warm clean jazz to blues, rock and beyond, the guitar simply sings out and begs for you to play some more. 
Our Korina V comes to us in incredibly clean condition. There is not a single visible nick ding or scratch to be found on the guitar. The Gold "V" below the bridge does show some tarnish sadly...and there is a very small amount of tarnish on the pick up covers, but beyond this the guitar is absolutely dead mint clean. 
It's been freshly set up with D'Addario .10-.46 strings in standard tuning with a straight neck and screaming action. Ships in original Hamer hard shell case and includes original Hamer owners manual specific to this guitar (serial number written in owners manual)

description:

This guitar features a solid alder body, maple neck and fretboard. Equipped with Fender Texas Special single coils in the neck and middle position, a Seymour Duncan Pearly gates humbucker in bridge. Controlled by a master volume, 2-tone controls and 5-way blade switch. The 25.5” scale length neck has black dot inlays and 22 medium jumbo frets with a 'Modern C' shape neck profile. This guitar was modified before we got it, it started its life as a SSS setup with a synthetic bone nut. the pick guard, and pickups were changed along with the nut. The nut job does not look great and is little high, this is the main reason we are only listing this in good condition and AS IS. It does have a couple dings still. The nut has been inspected by our luthier and could be replaced/ done right, it is still absolutely playable and set up with the nut in its current configuration. Vintage ESP Random Star in Purple Bengal Tiger finish made in 1982 with Coffin hardshell case. This guitar features an alder body, a maple neck and ebony fretboard. Equipped with the original Fender grey bottom single-coil pickups dating to 1975 complete with the original pots that date to the 51st week of 1974. The 25.5" scale length neck dates to 1974 and has a medium C shape neck profile and has been professionally re-fretted which is often necessary with vintage Stratocaster's from this time period and gives the guitar an entirely new life! The original "F" Style tuning machines and original 6-saddle Fender bridge are in fantastic condition and keep excellent tuning stability. The original 3-ply white pick-guard shows no signs of shrinking and has no cracks or splitting at the screw holes and is complete along with the matching white original Fender knobs, switch tip and pickups covers.

This guitar is in excellent condition with only minor surface scratches and very little wear. The re-fret was very well done and allows the guitar to play perfectly with low action and no string buzz or dead spot. Freshly re-strung with 10-46 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning this guitar plays fantastic, looks great and sounds incredible! Comes with Fender late 60's/early 70's hardshell case with orange interior.

title: Walrus Audio Monument Tremolo 2010s Graphic
description:
Inspired by the beautifully jagged, red-sand desert landscape of Monument Valley, the Monument Tremolo is both a harmonic, and standard tremolo that produces a rich, luscious, warm pulsating modulation capable of peaks and valleys as smooth or as jagged as the real ones that our dear mother nature created long ago.

With different combinations of the rate, division and shape knobs and tap tempo, everything from traditional tremolo to inspiring unique waveforms will help you carve new paths that you won’t hear anywhere else.

Harken back to vintage tones inspired by Fender Brownface amps in Harmonic mode. A low-pass and high-pass version of your guitar signal are modulated opposite of each other, or 180º out of phase (high and low frequencies rise and fall opposite of each other). The result is a warm, almost “chewy” tremolo.

The Division knob can be set to quarter, triplet, eighth and sixteenth.

Wave shapes can be controlled via the Shape knob. You can move between Sine, Square, Ramp, Lumps and Monument Mode (random).

A special feature on the Monument is the bypass switch also has a momentary function. When the switch is in off position, press and hold to temporarily activate the effect to add a moment of texture. Releasing the switch turns the effect off.

Setting the depth knob at 0 and the volume knob above unity creates a clean boost.

title: Pigtronix Philosopher King
description:
The Pigtronix Philosopher King is a polyphonic amplitude synthesizer that combines the award-winning compression / sustainer circuit from the Philosophers Tone with a next generation envelope generator. Building upon the technology of the Pigtronix Attack Sustain, the Philosopher King takes tone several steps further with a full set of ADSR controls including hold level, release time, one-shot mode, selectable auto reset, and expression pedals for swell and fade times.

With the Swell and Fade functions switched off, the Philosopher King provides transparent optical compression with endless sustain on tap. Adjustable compression (ratio), sustain (threshold) and treble (2k cut / boost) controls allow the musician to tailor the nature of the effect to meet the needs of the material at hand. From a subtle dash of added punch to massive, over-the-top howling sustain, the Philosopher King delivers clean, powerful optical compression. The grit control blends in a layer of sweet harmonic distortion that plays nice with other gain pedals as well as amplifier-generated tube distortion.

The Philosopher Kings swell function provides a pick triggered volume swell effect. The volume swell can be reset at any moment by muting or held open by continuous playing. This slow gear type effect is smooth and controllable with variable timing from extremely fast to very slow.

The fade function can be used independently of the swell and is also pick triggered. A major new feature of the decay cycle in this pedal is the ability to fade out from peak level only partially, bringing the audio down to a predetermined level, set by the hold control. The hold level is then maintained until the player releases the note to close the cycle. With the auto reset turned on, the cycle will begin again immediately, creating undulating amplitude modulation and even pulsating tremolo stutter effects at faster decay settings. With the auto-reset turned off, the player determines the exact timing for the beginning of the next cycle.

Another new feature is the one shot mode, which causes the Philosopher King to run through the swell / fade / hold / release cycle regardless of what is played after the cycle is triggered. In this mode, the Philosopher King creates complex waves of amplitude modulation on top of the music coming from your instrument. A trigger input jack allows the swell and fade functions to be controlled by an external source such as a band mate or drum track.

Inspired by the EH Attack Decay as well as our own Pigtronix Attack Sustain, the Philosopher King is a state-of-the-art stompbox unmatched in its ability to re-shape the essential nature of any sound source.

Features:

  • Optical Compressor with Outrageous Sustain
  • Synthesizer Style ADSR for Guitar
  • POLYPHONIC (works with chords)
  • Pick Triggered Volume Swell
  • One Shot Mode & Auto Reset
  • Grit control for smooth Distortion
  • 2K Treble Cut / Boost
  • Expression Pedals for Swell and Fade Times
  • Trigger Input for External Rhythm Source
  • Pigtronix 18VDC adapter included
  • Circuit Design by Howard Davis
  • TRUE BYPASS
  • Chassis Size = 7.4" x 4.6" x 1.5"

title: Fender 70th Anniversary Esquire 2020 Seafoam Green
description:
Fender 70th Anniversary Esquire 2020 Seafoam Green

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this beautiful 70th Anniversary Esquire from Fender.

The very first solid-body electric guitar offered by Fender in 1950 was the Esquire. With an elegant single-cutaway silhouette, adjustable 3-saddle bridge and a lone, repurposed lap-steel pickup in the bridge position – the Esquire laid the groundwork for all solid body electric guitars to follow and foreshadowed its more famous sibling, the Telecaster.

Like the earliest Esquire models, the 70th Anniversary Esquire features a pine body – a lightweight wood known for punchy and complex tone – and upgrades it with our roasting treatment, greatly improving the resonance of the body. Other features include a lacquer finish, thick “U”-shaped neck, Tim Shaw-designed Esquire bridge pickup – inspired by an original ’50 Esquire from Songbirds Museum in Chattanooga, TN - special anniversary neck plate and tweed case.
Our Esquire came to us in excellent condition with out a single visible nick, ding or scratch! While we stray away from using the term "mint" this guitar is definitely what we'd call a case queen. Obviously cherished and loved by the collector who had it previously. The factory foam wrap and tags are still on the case handle! The guitar includes all original hang tags and COA. Ships in it's original Fender tweed hard shell case.

title: Jackson USA Fusion HSS Bikini Beach Graphic 1990 OHSC Vintage
description:
Vintage Jackson USA Fusion HSS With Bikini Beach Graphic, Ebony fretboard and Floyd Rose made in 1990 with Jackson hard shell case. This guitar features an alder body, a bolt-on 2-piece quartersawn maple neck and ebony fretboard. Equipped with a Seymour Duncan TB4 Trembucker in the bridge, two Jackson single coils in middle/neck, controlled with a master volume pot, master tone pot, 5-way blade switch and a 2-way mini toggle 'wah' switch. The 24.75” scale length neck has mother of pearl shark fin inlays, 24 jumbo frets on a 12”-16” compound radius fingerboard and a speed neck profile. The hardware is comprised black Jackson sealed die-cast tuning machines, a matching Jackson branded licensed Floyd Rose recessed floating tremolo bridge, locking Floyd Rose nut and knurled black dome knobs.

 

 This guitar was reportedly signed By Ozzy Osbourne, Randy Castillo, Geezer Butler and Joe Holmes. It is very difficult to truly authenticate signatures, but they all appear to be legitimate when compared to multiple examples of each musician's penmanship. This guitar is in good condition, it has some cracking / chips in finish on back side, it had some minor de-lamination in a few parts of the finish which were repaired by our professional luthier (see pics)

Guitar is freshly setup and restrung with 9–42 strings and includes original Jackson hard shell case.

title: Marshall DSL 100 H - 100 Watt - Tube Amplifier - 2014 - In Excellent Condition - Never Gigged!
description:
Marshall DSL 100 H - 100 Watt - Tube Amplifier - 2014 

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this ripping Marshall DSL 100H. 

This formidable 100W head delivers that unmistakable Marshall tone with ease, giving you the flexibility and confidence to take to the stage. Crank it up or dial it back. The DSL100H takes it all in its stride.  With the ability to switch to half power mode without affecting sound quality, you can match your sound to your environment.  With individual reverb settings per channel, an FX loop, presence and resonance, your sonic possibilities are endless.  Move between clean, crunch and overdrive with the two footswitchable channels. Each one comes with a further two modes for true versatility.

Our DSL 100H came to us from a studio setting where it had rarely, if ever, been used! Its is in remarkably clean shape, nearly brand new! Ships with 2 button Marshall foot switch and IEC power cable.

description:
Esp LTD Michael Wilton Signature model in gloss black finish with “Skulls” signed by the members of Queensryche made in Korea in 2006. There are a few variations of these guitars but they all share the same amazing quality, craftmanship and playability.

The guitar is remarkably versatile in regards to tone. Loaded with a Seymour Duncan TB4 in the bridge which is coil tapped in position 2 on the 5 way blade switch. Hardware is set up with an original Floyd Rose locking tremolo system for the ultimate in tuning stability. Sperzel locking tuners round out the headstock giving you guaranteed stability whether the nut is locked or unlocked.

The guitar is in Excellent condition, however it does have some light surface scratches and a small split in the finish at the Floyd recess. It's been freshly set up and restrung with D'Addario 09-42 strings in standard tuning. And includes a Gator TSA hard shell case.

title: Zion Z-Master Prototype Masterbuilt 1 of 1 - 2003 - Natural
description:
Zion Z Mater Prototype 1 of 1 master built made in 2003 in natural finish. This beautiful guitars features a swamp ash body, highly figured flame maple top, and a solid birds eye maple neck. This is the very first prototype of the Z Master model which later went on to be a built to order option by Zion guitars. Equipped with Lindy Frallin P-90 pickups controlled by a master volume, two tone knobs and a 3-way pickup selector switch. The 25.5” scale length neck has very highly figured birds eye maple wood grain, a 12” fingerboard radius, abalone dot inlays and 22 medium jumbo frets. The locking Sperzel tuning machines and 6-saddle string through bridge have excellent tuning stability and resonate very well through the chambered body.

This guitar was extremely well made with very close attention to detail, this is a fantastic instrument! The guitar has been kept in excellent condition however there are some small scratches near the input jack as well as very light surface scratches and belt buckle marks (see photos). Freshly re-strung with 9-42 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning, this guitar plays great. Looks killer and sounds incredible! This is a very finely crafted guitar that was made with care and precision by a master luthier.

model: Pro-Mod So-Cal Style 1 HSH FR M
title: Charvel Pro-Mod So-Cal Style 1 HSH FR M 2021 Slime Green (B-Stock)
description:
Charvel Pro Mod ~ So-Cal Style ~ 1HSH FR E ~ Slime Green (B-Stock)

More comfortable than an overstuffed armchair, the So-Cal body is sleekly sculpted out of alder and paired with a rock-solid bolt-on maple neck with a pair of graphite-reinforcement rods to handle the ravages of the road and climate. A conveniently located heel-mount spoke wheel allows for rapid truss rod tweaks, even in between songs. Engineered for effortlessly nimble playing, the speed neck profile and 12"-16" compound radius ebony fingerboard with 22 frets is perfect for all styles of play — from low end riffing to soaring leads with worry-free upper-register bends.

Hot-rodded for unparalleled performance and sound, this instrument hosts a high-output Seymour Duncan Distortion TB-6 humbucking bridge pickup, Seymour Duncan Custom Flat Strat SSL-6 Single-Coil middle pickup and a Seymour Duncan Distortion SH-6N humbucking neck pickup. This powerful pickup trio produces aggressive harmonics in the bridge position for distinguished blues and metal runs, the perfect blend of heightened output and springy Stratocaster attitude in the middle, and the ideal searing, crunchy tone for brazen leads in the neck.


Extensive tonal variations are on top with a five-way blade pickup switch, volume control and a no-load tone control that operates like a standard tone control from positions one through nine, and removes itself from the circuit at position ten for transparent sound, letting the full natural voice of the guitar shine through. Scream or rumble with the Floyd Rose 1000 Series double-locking tremolo system without sacrificing tuning stability or the pinpoint intonation.

Born from a love of high-speed playing and designed to inspire, the Pro-Mod So-Cal Style 1 HSH FR E is wrapped in slime green finish and features a white pickguard and chrome hardware.

This Model is B-Stock for a hairline finish imperfection at the neck pocket and some black specs in the paint under clearcoat(see pic), it is 100% functional and playable, passing discount onto you! Guitar has been completely gone through and setup. It is Sold AS IS.

title: Fender Vintage Pro Reverb Black Face 40-watt 2x12 Tube Combo Amp with Reverb And Vibrato 1966 USA
description:
Vintage Fender Pro Reverb Black Face 40-watt 2x12 Tube Combo Amp with Reverb And Vibrato made in 1966 USA in Very Good condition. Tested, 100% operational. Plus some vintage NOS glass! (see pics and Specs)
It is missing the top rear panel.

“The Blackface Fender Pro Reverb has skyrocketed in popularity over the years, though it took a while to get there. Considered "too weak" for the mid-1960s market, today they're beloved for their signature Blackface sound and breakup at much more manageable volumes than a Twin Reverb or the piggyback amps. Standing in at 40 watts with two 12" speakers, the Pro Reverb is essentially a dialed-back Twin -- smaller transformers, half the power tubes and a tube rectifier produce a saggier sound that drives much earlier. This fantastic stage amp has seen a renaissance over the last couple decades and has become a wildly popular stage amp for bands touring mid-sized clubs.”

Our 66 Pro Reverb boasts the original 152P5D / 606542 Power Transformer, 125C1A / - 606-6-02 Choke and 022848 / -606-6-04 Output Transformer as well as the 125A20B / -- 606542 Reverb Driver. 

The original 12" speakers have been replaced at some point with Eminence 4512415 Fender brown and tan label speakers manufactured for Fender in mid 90's for their Blues Jr. series amplifiers.

All internal components are documented in the photos above. Sadly; a former owner, 'Ken Burch' felt the need to scratch his name into the back of the chassis. Beyond that the amp is in remarkable condition! Sounds incredible!

model: UE 305 Multi Effect Pedal 100% Analog Delay, Chorus and Compressor
title: Ibanez UE 305 Multi Effect Pedal 100% Analog Delay, Chorus and Compressor - 1984 - RARE!
description:
Ibanez UE 305 Multi Effect Pedal 100% Analog Delay, Chorus and Compressor - 1984 - RARE!

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this unique and rare Ibanez UE 305 Analog multi effects pedal. These were only manufactured in very small numbers in 1984 and 1985 making them difficult gems to find!

Ibanez's UE 305 is a multi effect for the ages, combining three excellent pedals from Ibanez’s golden age of effects into one large enclosure!

The Ibanez 9 Series pedals are still some of the most sought-after effects around, and the UE 305 gives you three of the best from this series. We start off with the CP-9 Compressor/Limiter, which is a pretty musical comp, with a bit of a mid-boost and a little bit of attitude. A straight transparent compressor it is not, but gives you some grit if you crank the Threshold knob up past 3:00 or so. It’s quiet, though, which is nice, and has great sustain as well. 

Up next is the AD-9 Analog Delay, which is a fantastic echo effect, one that is revered by delay enthusiasts the world over. With simple Delay Time, Delay Level and Repeat controls, there’s not too much to figure out with this one, but a lot of warm and inviting analog echoes waiting to be heard.

Finally, the UE 305 features the CS-9 Stereo Chorus last in the lineup. Width adjusts the depth or amplitude of the LFO wave that controls the delay time of the chorus effect, while Speed controls the rate of the delay time. Simple, no nonsense chorus sounds, the CS-9 fits in perfectly here with the other two effects, bringing that same analog warmth and lushness to its output effect tone. 

Each of these effects are bypassable with their own individual footswitches, or you can combine them in any configuration you choose. A Master switch bypasses the entire unit all at once, so you don’t have to waste time shutting off each section one by one.

Manufactured in small numbers during 1984-85, the UE 305 has become a rare pedal in vintage collector’s collections. The UE 305 also features an Effects Loop to add in more fun toys, as well as THREE (yes, 3) Output jacks, to send the signals wherever you want them to go. Super-fun, pretty nostalgic and still sounding great, this monster pedal from Ibanez gives you the best analog of an effects era, all wrapped up in one neat, tidy package.

Charvel Pro Mod ~ So-Cal Style ~ 1HSH FR E ~ Robin's Egg Blue (B-Stock)

More comfortable than an overstuffed armchair, the So-Cal body is sleekly sculpted out of alder and paired with a rock-solid bolt-on maple neck with a pair of graphite-reinforcement rods to handle the ravages of the road and climate. A conveniently located heel-mount spoke wheel allows for rapid truss rod tweaks, even in between songs. Engineered for effortlessly nimble playing, the speed neck profile and 12"-16" compound radius ebony fingerboard with 22 frets is perfect for all styles of play — from low end riffing to soaring leads with worry-free upper-register bends.

Hot-rodded for unparalleled performance and sound, this instrument hosts a high-output Seymour Duncan Distortion TB-6 humbucking bridge pickup, Seymour Duncan Custom Flat Strat SSL-6 Single-Coil middle pickup and a Seymour Duncan Distortion SH-6N humbucking neck pickup. This powerful pickup trio produces aggressive harmonics in the bridge position for distinguished blues and metal runs, the perfect blend of heightened output and springy Stratocaster attitude in the middle, and the ideal searing, crunchy tone for brazen leads in the neck.


Extensive tonal variations are on top with a five-way blade pickup switch, volume control and a no-load tone control that operates like a standard tone control from positions one through nine, and removes itself from the circuit at position ten for transparent sound, letting the full natural voice of the guitar shine through. Scream or rumble with the Floyd Rose 1000 Series double-locking tremolo system without sacrificing tuning stability or the pinpoint intonation.

Born from a love of high-speed playing and designed to inspire, the Pro-Mod So-Cal Style 1 HSH FR E is wrapped in Robin’s Egg Blue and features a white pickguard and chrome hardware.

title: Marshall JCM 2550 / 2558 Silver Jubilee 50 Watt 2 x 12 Combo VINTAGE 1987
description:
Marshall JCM 2550 / 2558 Silver Jubilee 50 Watt 2 x 12 Combo VINTAGE 1987

Just in at Diablo Guitars is this rare and killer sounding Marshall Silver Jubilee 2 x 12 Combo. 

In 1987 Marshall brought out its Silver Jubilee series for its 25th anniversary. In the ‘80s, the hot-rodded Marshall was all the craze, with Marshalls being modified in all kinds of ways around the world for more preamp-gain as well as options such as direct outs and effects loops. Again, the desire has always been and continued to be to get more distortion at lower levels and this was before the era of the hot plate or a power soak of any kind. Marshall set out to produce its own hot-rodded from the factory amplifier and the various 50 and 100 watt Silver Jubilee amps were born. They looked cool as well with chrome mirrored panels and unique silver tolex.

These amps have their own unique sonic structure and are extremely versatile. The tone circuits worked much more dramatically when one would turn up or down the tone shaping controls (bass, mids, treble, presence). More gain was also produced, thanks to a diode circuit that provided additional distortion from one of the gain stages. Because of the design of the amp itself, which really has a well-designed preamp tone stage in particular, the Jubilee amps enjoy widespread popularity and have become extremely sought after and collectable today.

The modern features such as an effects loop, direct out, a channel switching modes brought further versatility to the amp. This series does a jaw dropping job of capturing the essence of the earlier Marshall tones as well as capturing the very best of the modern higher-gain sounds. Marshall did a beautiful job refining this preamp circuit and the design. Since the Jubilee series were newly-tuned circuits, Marshall seemed to put more care into the final tone and design of these models than they did with the regular JCM 800 line when the cost-cutting went into effect!

The amp is in very good condition. It's been fully serviced and sounds incredible! There are some rips in the tolex all documented in the photos above. It has signs of general wear and tear and is also missing the silver mounting caps for the top handle. Amp will be shipped with included Marshall foot switch.

  • A favorite guitar amplifier of rock guitarists including Slash
  • 2-channel, 50-watt all-tube amplifier includes high-/low-output switching
  • Decked out in dazzling silver vinyl and outfitted with vintage appointments
  • Loaded with 2 x 12" original G12 Vintage Celestion Speakers

title: ESP Custom Shop Prototype Gus G Owned Signature Model Used W/Firewind & Ozzy Osbourne Black 2012
description:
ESP Custom Shop Gus G NT-III Signature Model Prototype made in 2012 owned and played by Gus in Firewind and Ozzy Osboune. This guitar was Gus G’s number one axe for a long period of time and can be seen in countless live performances, video interviews, clinics, and in the Guitar World magazine article included with this listing. This guitar made in 2012 was a prototype to Gus G’s signature model that was released in 2014 which saw the change of 22 frets to 24 frets using the same Star NT shape and in satin black finish.  Any footage of Gus using a 24 fret signature model in satin black was THIS actual guitar. Check out some of the youtube links that I have provided below.

This guitar is in the same condition and state as when I received it from Gus, as I wanted to keep the same tour wear, vibe and patina as it had come fresh off of tour. The beat up case with flight check stickers, the tape to hold guitar picks to throw out to fans during performances, and even the used strings and dirty frets I have left all intact. Ordinarily I would clean up everything but I wanted to keep the guitar 100% how I got it, I am happy to clean up as I do all of my other guitars if requested.

The specs of  the guitar are an alder body with maple neck-thru and bound rosewood fretboard. The neck is 25.5” scale length with a 12” radius and thin U shape equipped with 24 extra jumbo frets. The guitar has Gus G’s signature Seymour Duncan Fire Blackouts, controlled by a master volume with a 3-way pickup selector switch and a 2-Way BMP-1 preamp switch. The guitar has black hardware with locking sperzel tuners, and locking Tone Pros bridge & stop tailpiece.

This guitar comes with a signed magazine featuring Gus G on the cover and has an in depth interview with Gus which features several photos of THIS guitar. Also included is Gus G’s guitar pick, and I am also happy to make a COA if requested. If you would like additional information on how I acquired the guitar or any additional verification please contact me (serious inquiries only!) -Parker Lundgren

title: Jackson Pro Series RR24 Rhoads 2021 Maul Crackle Brand New
description:
Jackson's first customer was the legendary guitarist Randy Rhoads, who asked the company to create a model that met the demands of his technically-challenging playing along with visual panache. His famed Rhoads model has continued to evolve ever since in order to meet and exceed the needs of players who came of age listening to his groundbreaking work.

A proud claimant to the throne of high-tech guitars, the Jackson® Pro Series Rhoads RR24 Crackle pairs a basswood body to a through-body maple neck with a pair of graphite rods for reinforcement against the assaults of temperature and humidity. The speedy neck profile is engineered for blazing guitar work, removing any obstacles to fleet-fingered playing and granting easier access to the upper frets. A 12”-16” compound radius bound ebony fingerboard is also engineered for highly technical lightspeed playing—more curved by the nut for comfortable chording, it flattens out as you move up the neck for increasingly fast playing speed and wide bends without fretting out.

Direct mount Seymour Duncan® JB TB-4 bridge and Seymour Duncan ’59 SH-1N neck pickups combine for an incredibly versatile voice, from searing heavy tones with hot-rodded output to creamy leads and thick rhythms with plenty of definition. Three-way pickup toggle switching, single volume and single tone knobs provide flexible tonal control, while the Floyd Rose® 1000 Series double-locking tremolo system allows for distinguished flutters and aggressive dive bombs without losing tuning stability.

The most recognizable of Jackson’s myriad offerings, the Pro RR24 Crackle boasts the familiar aesthetics that keep Jackson axes in high-demand for performing guitarists. From the screaming-metal Lightning or Maul Crackle finish, pearloid sharkfin inlays, reverse pointed 6-in-line color matched crackle headstock and revolutionary body design, this instrument is very distinctly a Jackson creation.

Jackson guitars don’t just push the envelope, they annihilate it.

title: Bare Knuckle Aftermath Set 2021 Burnt Chrome Battleworn
description:
Bare Knuckle Aftermath Set 2021 Burnt Chrome Battleworn

Diablo Guitars Covers ALL VAT Tax and International Shipping for the customer as these pickups are made in the UK

The Aftermath is perfect for the modern metal guitarist, with accelerated bass response for exceptionally fast tracking of high-speed staccato riffing. It has a crushing mid range and precise high-end articulation.

With a symmetrically hand-wound twin screw coil design, the Aftermath bridge is powered by 3 custom size ceramic magnets. The bottom-end responds quickly to pick attack and tracks fast riffing extremely accurately, mids are focused and intense for ultimate punch no matter how dense the mix or how low the tuning, and highs are precise and articulate. With a more compressed dynamic, single notes have masses of sustain while the front of the note is clear-cut and defined even under extreme amounts of gain.

The Aftermath neck humbucker is Alnico V powered and voiced for fat, powerful clean tones, fluid vocal-like sustain when driven hard and good balance with the bridge humbucker.

As with all Bare Knuckle humbuckers, 4 conductor hook-up not only allows access to standard series (humbucking) tone but also parallel wiring (still hum cancelling) or selection of either individual coil for total versatility.

title: Bare Knuckle PG Blues Set 2021 Aged Nickel
description:
Bare Knuckle PG Blues Set 2021 Aged Nickel

Diablo Guitars Covers ALL VAT Tax and International Shipping for the customer as these pickups are made in the UK

Our PG Blues humbucker is designed to replicate the tones of Peter Green's famous '59 Les Paul (hence the name!) complete with the legendary “out of phase” tone achieved when both pickups are on.

The PG Blues humbucker set features Alnico II sand cast magnets, scatterwound bridge coils of 42AWG plain enamel wire and uniquely wound Heavy Formvar neck coils for the famous “out of phase” mid-position, when both humbuckers are on together. Vintage-correct solid nickel silver baseplates and covers, along with totally unpotted coils, all add to the vowel-like vocal delivery, bright yet sweet highs, warm bass and trademark “out of phase” tone.

Individually, the bridge humbucker is pure '59 PAF in tone with all the touch sensitive response you would expect from unpotted coils. The PG Blues neck humbucker, although wound out of phase with the bridge, retains a wonderful pure and fat tone of its own both, clean and with overdrive.

From haunting ambient lead lines and delicate chording to all-out blues rock, the PG Blues humbuckers are for players looking for authentic vintage tone with a unique edge.

title: Bare Knuckle Cold Sweat Set 2021 Aged Black
description:
Bare Knuckle Cold Sweat Set 2021 Aged Black

Diablo Guitars Covers ALL VAT Tax and International Shipping for the customer as these pickups are made in the UK

The Cold Sweat humbucker is a tight and percussive ceramic powered humbucker with a high resonant peak, producing clear, detailed treble response and smooth mids.

The custom sized ceramic magnet gives the Cold Sweat humbucker a more controlled dynamic with stacks of output and sustain. The mix of ceramic powered bridge and Alnico V powered neck gives a broad palette of clean and driven tones which creates the perfect tone for a variety of modern rock styles.

The neck humbucker is very popular among shred players for its articulate but fluid tone, and it is ideal for effortless sweep picking; the bridge pickup is also known for its precise attack. Pick harmonics jump out and the whole feel is very touch sensitive, especially when used with high-gain. The powerful bass and treble response of the bridge humbucker has the effect of slightly scooping the mids, which creates a very precise and rich tone with masses of depth.

The Cold Sweat humbuckers are absolutely perfect for pushing a tube amp into natural overdrive, and they will also maintain superb definition with the full saturation of a high-gain amp.

title: Bare Knuckle Rebel Yell Set 2021 Aged Zebra
description:
Bare Knuckle Rebel Yell Set 2021 Aged Zebra

Diablo Guitars Covers ALL VAT Tax and International Shipping for the customer as these pickups are made in the UK

The Rebel Yell pickup was created with Billy Idol guitarist Steve Stevens, who wanted metal and impact but with a tone that cleans up well when backing off the volume.

“The Rebel Yell just growls with an even harmonic richness that I never hear in other pickups. It's so full of clear bottom and perfect pick attack. These pickups are in a whole other league - they're the real deal!”

Steve Stevens.

When Steve first came to Bare Knuckle he was adamant that the signature pickups he wanted were not just 'another metal pickup'. They had to be capable of a whole lot more. This kicked off a year of development and road testing while Steve was on a Billy Idol tour. Five of Steve’s Les Pauls were used as the vehicles for the design, and Steve also spent many hours in the studio testing the pickups. This extensive testing culminated in the Rebel Yell humbucker signature set.

Closer offset coils of 43 AWG plain enamel wire retain the mid range punch of the hotter Nailbomb but produce a tighter bass response with cleaner highs and more presence. This gives the pickup an organic voice with plenty of impact, perfect for any player wanting a progressive humbucker rich in harmonic overtones and wide pick dynamics. Steve uses his volume pot a lot when he plays, so it was important that the Rebel Yell cleans up well when backing off the volume, on top of being able to push a tube amp hard for a fully saturated overdrive.

title: Bare Knuckle The Mule Set 2021 Aged Black & Gold
description:
Bare Knuckle The Mule Set 2021 Aged Black & Gold

Diablo Guitars Covers ALL VAT Tax and International Shipping for the customer as these pickups are made in the UK

The Mule has a classic 'Patent Applied For' vintage tone with exceptionally balanced frequency response and more than enough power for almost any application.

The Mule humbuckers are built and voiced as faithful reproductions of the best sounding late '59 PAFs with a differing number of turns of vintage correct 42 AWG plain enamel wire on each coil. The result is outstanding clarity and extended dynamic range. The solid nickel silver baseplate and cover are exact replicas along with the butyrate bobbins, maple spacers, nickel-plated slugs and Fillister no.5 pole screws. Sand cast Alnico IV magnets give The Mule faster response in the bass, fuller mids and better control in the high end. Even at low levels of gain, smooth harmonic feedback which is full of overtones is possible, while clean sounds have depth and unmistakable vintage character. The idea of these pickups is to have a vocal tone that’s expressive and clear, while driving amps commandingly into overdrive when required.

The Ragnarok is a chunky, fat sounding pickup that’s also devastatingly tight and aggressive; a hot ceramic pickup with a smooth top end and incredible clarity.

“The Ragnarok is aggressive. In a way, it is a response to the very balanced nature of the Juggernaut. I wanted once again to work with both Tim and Nolly to create a pickup that I felt hadn't been made yet, this time aiming for the more angry and compressed side of the spectrum. Misha Mansoor.

model: Vintage 1964 Band Master Black Face 100 Watt with Piggy Back 2 x 12" Cab
title: Fender Vintage 1964 Band Master Black Face Modified to 100 Watt with Piggy Back 2 x 12" Cab - RARE
description:
Fender Vintage 1964 Band Master "Blackface" Modified to 100 Watt with Piggy Back 2 x 12" Cab - RARE

This is a rare and clean example of the "Blackface" Fender Bandmaster. Despite it's age it's in quite good condition as detailed in the photos above. The unique thing about this particular head is that it is not the traditional 40 watt version of these amps that were manufactured from 1964 through 1967 before the "Silverface" era began. A professional upgrade has been made and this amp is now loaded with 4 6L6 JJ's in it's power stage offering a clean 100 watts of pure clarity and headroom.

The amp sounds fantastic, all the depth and character you'd expect from a Blackface Era Band Master. The cab is completely stock (more details below) and also sounds magnificent. The amp handles pedals remarkably well. It's just gorgeous top to bottom whether you're plugged straight in or running through several pedals to create various drives, delays or modulations. 

The head and piggy back cab are sold as a set. We apologize but we will not sell them as separate components.

We do NOT have the vintage footswitch for the vibrato on/off feature. It will need to be purchased separately should you want one. 

The amp's serial number is A 03209 - Stamped at the right rear upper corner of the chassis and pictured above. Using this serial number we were able to date the amp as a 1964.  

The 12" Speakers in the enclosure appear to be "Fender Blue Label" era based on the look of the magnets and the center spot which the label would surround. They have the "Swiss Cheese" frame further indicating that they are of that era. The cones however appear to be a vintage 60's era JBL as they have the large aluminum center dome. As the drivers do not appear to be the JBL style of that era it's a bit of a mystery. Fender like Marshall was very prone to "using what we've got on hand" in the 1960's, so subtle variances may occur build to build. All indicators point to these being vintage speakers and more than likely the speakers the cab shipped with. Sadly as the labels are missing (see photos above) it's very difficult to truly date or verify them beyond the tell tale clues we've listed above.

Once you tune the EverTune® F6 bridge, it will never go out of tune, making this DK Modern the perfect instrument for both the studio and live. Even if the van breaks down on the way to your next gig, you can still show up late, skip the soundcheck and take the stage with confidence.

title: ‘70s Fender Musicmaster Duo-Sonic Mustang Case Music Master Duosonic Red Interior Short-Scale
description:
‘70s Fender Musicmaster Duo-Sonic Mustang Hard Shell Case Music Master Duosonic Red Interior Short-Scale Guitar Vintage 1970s

This case is in excellent condition considering it's age. We dated it based on the case logo and interior. The "Made in USA" and circle over "R" appeared first in 1973 following the Non Underscored Fender logo that adorned these cases until 1972. In 1979 Fender went to more of a Burgundy colored interior. This case features a dark orange interior and lock in leather "neck strap" snapping belt; dating it to the 73-78 era Fender Case.

title: Fender Limited Edition Custom Shop '55 Reissue Stratocaster Relic Blonde 2015
description:
Fender Limited Edition Custom Shop ’55 Stratocaster in relic Blonde finish made in 2015. This guitar features a heavily relic’d 1955 style Stratocaster with aged Nickel hardware. Equipped with Fender Custom Shop hand-wound ’55 single coil pickups controlled by a master volume & two tone knobs along with a 5-way pickup selector switch. This guitar has a very old school vintage tone that cuts through with distortion and is crystal clear for clean tones. The aged Nickel hardware is very convincing and looks just like hardware that came off of a 50’s Strat that was found in a barn or was used on tour. Despite the aged look the custom shop vintage -style single-line tuning machines and synchronized tremolo function very well and hold excellent tuning stability. The 25.5 scale length neck has the worn in feel of a well-loved vintage Strat and a full feeling 50’s U-Shape neck profile.

This guitar is in mint condition despite being a factory heavy relic and has been freshly re-strung with 10-46 gauge strings and setup in standard tuning. This guitar looks, feels and plays just like a 1955 Fender Stratocaster that has aged perfectly yet is still playable with a full life ahead. Comes with the original “Limited Edition” White Tolex with red velvet interior hardshell case, COA, warranty card, bridge cover, Fender Custom Shop polish cloth and other factory case candy!

model: D12X1 from the Jeff Loomis Collection
title: Martin D12X1  Jeff Loomis Collection Used in Nevermore 2009 Natural Satin Finish Autographed
description:
Martin D12X1 from the Jeff Loomis Collection 2009 Natural Satin Finish

Diablo Guitars is extremely proud to be making available a series of guitars from the personal collection of Seattle's own Jeff Loomis. Jeff is best known for his incredible guitar work with Sanctuary, Nevermore and Arch Enemy. He's also continued to create, inspire and wow both players and fans alike with his 2 stunning solo releases. His forthcoming solo release is bound to be another showcase of his remarkable playing and song craft. Jeff has decided to part ways with some of these gorgeous guitars in favor of some new acquisitions; something we can all relate to as nothing is quite as exciting as a new guitar in your hands! We're stoked that he's chosen to trust the team here at Diablo to find his personal guitars new and loving owners. Jeff has taken the time to autograph press shots, and include tins of 12 of his signature model picks from Dunlop which will be included with any of the guitars from his collection. These instruments were all meticulously gone through and set up to Jeff's standards before being released for sale. All of the guitars from this unique collection are simply fantastic. A must own for any player or especially any fan of Loomis' amazing playing.

This Martin 12-string was actually used by Jeff Loomis on one of Nevermore's albums "Obsidian Conspiracy on the track entitled "She Comes In Colors" and is a very cool collector's piece for any fan of Jeff Loomis and/or the band Nevermore. You can hear the song via the provided Youtube clip!


The 12-string Martin D12X1 acoustic guitar represents a fine example Martin's commitment to preserving the earth's dwindling resources and designing guitars that are within reach of every aspiring guitarist. Constructed with a combination of highly compressed wood fibers (high-pressure laminate, HPL) and traditional tonewoods, the D12X1 has the famous Martin sound and playability found in their more expensive guitars.

This gorgeous Martin 12 string came to us in excellent condition with no visible scratches or dings. There is some oxidation visible on the tuning machines (see pictures above). Freshly set up with D'Addario 12 (Light) Guage 12 string strings. Includes auto graphed press shot of Jeff Loomis and a Jeff Loomis collectable pic tin. The back of the headstock has also been autographed by Jeff.
